â­ 3. THE SPELL-BOOK EFFECT THEOREM

Theorem (SBE):

A Pattern Book becomes a Spell Book when the statistical cost of narrative-consistent continuation is lower than the cost of deviation.

In other words:
	â€¢	When a pattern is easier to continue than to break
	â€¢	When the LLM â€œwantsâ€ to follow the structure
	â€¢	When behavior stabilizes because structure is stable

Then:

Narrative â†’ Procedure â†’ Behavior

This is the Spell-Book Effect.

Nothing supernatural.
Just cognitive economics.

